# hilavitkutin — agent instructions

## What hilavitkutin is

hilavitkutin is a morsel-driven pipeline execution engine. Consumers
declare WorkUnits with typed read/write access sets; the engine
analyses them into phases/trunks/fibers, compiles per-core dispatch
programs, and runs them on a pre-allocated thread pool. Every crate
is `#![no_std]`, no `alloc`, no runtime spawn, no dynamic dispatch.

The canonical spec is
`design_rounds/202603181200_topic.hilavitkutin-design-consolidation.md`
(22 domains, 9 cross-domain resolutions). `mock/DESIGN.md.tmpl` and
`mock/PRINCIPLES.md.tmpl` are the map into that spec.

## Identity

{{crate_count}} crates, flat structure, four logical groupings:

**API (consumer-facing contracts).** `hilavitkutin-api` ships `WorkUnit`, `AccessSet`, `Column<T>`, `Resource<T>`, `Virtual<T>`, `Context`, `Contains`, and the platform contracts (`Clock`, `MemoryProvider`, `ThreadPool`).

**Engine (the scheduler and runtime).** `hilavitkutin` houses `plan` (phase, fiber, analysis, morsel, loading), `dispatch`, `resource`, `thread`, `strategy`, `adapt`, `scheduler`, `intrinsics`, and `platform`.

**Build-time (build-dep only, no runtime linkage).** `hilavitkutin-build` holds LLVM passes, MIR manipulation, cfg emission, PGO / BOLT workflows, and ExpandedLto pragma support. Consumer's `build.rs` uses this; the runtime crate never links to it.

**Extensions (standalone opt-in sub-libraries).** `hilavitkutin-ctx` is the provider-gated context framework, `hilavitkutin-persistence` is the generic hot/cold storage bridge, and `hilavitkutin-str` is the interned string system.

