## Where things live

- `docs/DESIGN.md` — generated, canonical architecture.
- `docs/STRUCTURE.md` + graph — generated, crate and item index.
- `mock/DESIGN.md.tmpl`, `mock/PRINCIPLES.md.tmpl`,
  `mock/WORKFLOW.md.tmpl` — authored sources.
- `mock/crates/*/DESIGN.md.tmpl` — per-crate deep dives.
- `mock/design_rounds/` — design round state machine. Do not
  rename files by hand; use `cargo mock lock` / `unlock` /
  `deprecate` / `close`.
- `mock/agent/` — these instructions. Edit templates here, not the
  generated files under `.claude/` or `.github/`.
- `mock/lints/` — repo-specific Rust lints compiled into `cargo
  mock`.

## What not to do

- Do not add `alloc`, `std`, `Vec`, `String`, `Box`, `dyn`, or
  `TypeId` to any `hilavitkutin*` crate.
- Do not introduce runtime spawn (`thread::spawn`, `tokio::spawn`,
  `async_std::spawn`). The pool is pre-allocated at plan time.
- Do not introduce runtime registration (`inventory::submit!`,
  `#[ctor]`, `#[distributed_slice]`). All WU composition is static.
- Do not use the dead vocabulary terms (`chain`, `chain_group`,
  `partition`, `archetype`, `entity`, `row`, `order`) for any
  engine-domain concept.
- Do not let `hilavitkutin-api` depend on `hilavitkutin`. The
  api is the contract; the engine is one implementation of it.
- Do not re-export arvo types through `hilavitkutin-api`. Consumers
  depend on arvo directly if they need it.
- Do not add concrete heap-backed collections to any crate. Plan
  structures are const-generic; runtime structures come from
  consumer-provided `MemoryProvider`.
- Do not edit files under `.claude/`, `.github/copilot-instructions.md`,
  `.github/instructions/`, `.github/skills/`, or `.github/hooks/`.
  They regenerate from `mock/agent/` on every `cargo mock`.
- Do not hand-rename `design_rounds/*.md` suffixes. Use the
  subcommands.
